# Next.js Intensive Rendering Constraints

Isolate high-frequency rendering workloads into optimized Client Components.

- ISOLATE high-frequency processing into dedicated, heavily memoized Client Components.
- NEVER use `useState` or `useReducer` for rapidly mutating telemetry data; store mutable data in `useRef` and interact directly with DOM/Canvas APIs when needed.
- NEVER import intensive rendering components directly into a Server Component.
- Mark intensive components with `"use client"`.
- Apply strict memoization (`React.memo`, `useMemo`, `useCallback`) to minimize unnecessary re-renders.
- Load intensive components with `next/dynamic` using `{ ssr: false }` to bypass SSR and protect initial payload performance.
